comments.body:
The 2nd half of the tests need to ensure they get a new fs instance each time.  Getting a new fs instance for all tests isn't a bad thing though.  If one test changes the internal state of the fs (say changeWorkingDirectory, etc), it can contaminate the other tests.  It frustrates the poor dev trying to figure out why their simple tests don't work -- hint: whose comment do you think that is? :)

Something like this is what I think is needed.
{code}
@Before
public void setupFs() {
  hdfs = ...;
  hftpFs = ...;
}
@After
public void resetFsCache() {
  FileSystem.closeAll();
}
{code}
